I often hear the argument "I don't want to change my lifestyle", when people argue against green policies. I think the pandemic is showing that "in the future, just about anything is possible", and sometimes, the effects are out of our control. If we think that a 4 month or one year lockdown is tough (while we all wait for a vaccine), then you are going to just hate it when half of Florida goes under water. Yes, the ice caps are melting.
At the very least, the pandemic has shown to us what can be achieved if everyone pulls together, on a global basis. And in that respect, the fight against the covid-19 virus and climate change are similar in that both needs to be done globally. A greener policy in one country is nullified if some other country can attract businesses with less strict environmental protection policies in place. No one country can "elect" to be absent from any accords.
I am not an alarmist. I am a realist. We have not seen the full effects of climate change. And when it happens, it is near irreversible. And I hope nobody will say "no one could have predicted ..."
Changing our lifestyle. It is no longer a choice.
